💪 Day 1 – Gym Workout Series | Chest & Shoulder Day

Starting off this series with one of my fav splits — Chest + Shoulders!
Before jumping into weights, I always do 5–10 minutes of dynamic stretching to warm up my upper body and avoid injury.

👉 Personally, for upper body workouts, I prefer lighter weights with higher reps — by lighter, I mean weights that challenge me in the last 2–3 reps.

⸻

🔥 Workout Breakdown:

1. Push-ups
• 3 sets × 10 reps
(Beginners: Start with knee push-ups and gradually work your way to regular push-ups)

2. Flat Bench Chest Press
• 3 sets × 12 reps
• Use moderate weight and focus on controlled full range of motion.

3. Incline Bench Chest Press
• 3 sets × 10 reps
• Targets the upper chest more effectively.

4. Cable Chest Fly (on Incline Bench)
• 3 sets × 10 reps
• Squeeze your chest at the top. Slow and mindful reps.

5. Dumbbell Shoulder Press
• 3 sets × 16 reps
• Use lighter weights, control movements, and focus on mind-muscle connection.
• Shoulders respond well to higher reps.

6. Dumbbell Side Raises
• 3 sets × 20 reps
• Same approach — light weight, high reps, full control.

⸻

✅ Keep your form clean. Train smart. Stay consistent.
